cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses privacy by design and the use of formal methods to support it. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation and availability of tools for formal methods. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as formal methods often involve the use of formal languages and logics. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as formal methods often involve the use of formal logics. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the application of formal methods to support privacy in various domains, which has societal implications.
